The paper deals with the performance of massive MIMO systems in a mobile scenario, which involves issues related to information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.MA), multimedia (cs.MM), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper discusses the impact of mobility on the performance of massive MIMO systems, which is a topic that is relevant to all these sub-categories. However, given the focus on channel state information (CSI) and power control update rates, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories.
